                <h2>Strawberry Drip System Specifications</h2>
                <ul class="check-list" style="margin-top:20px;">
                    <li>One or two laterals per bed, placed at 1–3" depth on raised beds</li>
                    <li>Emitter spacing: 4–8 inches for shallow-rooted strawberries</li>
                    <li>Flow rate: 0.16–0.30 GPH depending on bed width and soil type</li>
                    <li>Annual drip tape (replanted with crop) or multi-season lay-flat</li>
                    <li>Fertigation compatible with all standard berry nutrition programs</li>
                    <li>Pressure regulators at each row or zone head for slope compensation</li>
                </ul>
                <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary" style="margin-top:28px;display:inline-block;">Find a Dealer</a>
